 Because the center of the circle is on the x-axis, the center must be of the form $(x, 0)$. Let the radius be $r (\gt 0)$. <solution> Let the center of the circle be $(a,0)$. Using the distance formula, we can find the radius $r$ as follows:

\begin{align} r &=\sqrt{(a+3)^2+2^2} \\ &=\sqrt{(a+2)^2+3^2} \\ r^2&=(a+3)(a+3)+4 \\ &=(a+2)(a+2)+9 \\ r^2-r &=9 \\ r&=10 \end{align}

</solution> The radius of the circle is $\boxed{10}$. END

