&= \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \times \frac12 \begin{pmatrix}
x - y \\ y - z \\ z - x \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}
and thus
\[\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ -2 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix} \times \frac12 \begin{pmatrix}
x - y \\ y - z \\ z - x \end{pmatrix}.\]This is of the form $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} x_0 \\ y_0 \\ z_0 \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} x_1 \\ y_1 \\ z_1 \end{pmatrix} \times \mathbf{u},$ where $(x_0, y_0, z_0) \in \mathbb{R}^3$ and $\mathbf{u},$ $\mathbf{u} \neq \mathbf{0},$ is a vector in the plane spanned by the set of vectors satisfying $\mathbf{v} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v}$ being orthogonal to $\mathbf{w}.$  Thus the set of vectors satisfying $\mathbf{v} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{w}} \mathbf{v}$ orthogonal to $\mathbf{w}$ forms a plane, as desired.  It has equation $\boxed{2x - y + 2z - 16 = 0}.$
